<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<theorem xmlns="Theorem"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         type="Proposition"
         id="Thm_InvertibleMapsComposition"
         xsi:schemaLocation="Theorem file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle/mod/msm/NewSchemas/Theorem.xsd">
   <caption>Composition of invertible linear maps</caption>
   <associate type="Explanation">
      <info>
         <info.caption>
            <caption>Explanation for the conclusion of this proposition</caption>
         </info.caption>
         <para>
            <para.body>Conceptually the conclusion of this proposition is quite transparent: If we want to reverse the effect of the composite <math>
                  <latex>(T\Comp S)</latex>
               </math>, we can do so by first reversing the effect of <math>
                  <latex>T</latex>
               </math>, using <math>
                  <latex>T^{-1}</latex>
               </math>, and then reversing the effect of <math>
                  <latex>S</latex>
               </math>, using <math>
                  <latex>S^{-1}</latex>
               </math>. In other words:</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.display>
            <latex>S^{-1}\Comp T^{-1} \Comp T\Comp S = \Id[n]</latex>
         </math.display>
         <para>
            <para.body>Hence the claim.</para.body>
         </para>
      </info>
   </associate>
   <statement.theorem>
      <para>
         <para.body>If <math>
               <latex>S,T\from \RNr[n]\to \RNr[n]</latex>
            </math> are invertible linear transformations, then <math>
               <latex>(T\Comp S)</latex>
            </math> is also invertible and</para.body>
      </para>
      <math.display>
         <latex>(T\Comp S)^{-1} = S^{-1}\Comp T^{-1}</latex>
      </math.display>
   </statement.theorem>
   <proof>
      <proof.block>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>We need to show that the composite <math>
                     <latex>S^{-1}\Comp T^{-1}</latex>
                  </math> is the inverse of <math>
                     <latex>(T\Comp S)</latex>
                  </math>. To this end we compute:</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.array column="3">
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>(S^{-1}\Comp T^{-1})\Comp (T\Comp S)</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=	</text>
                     <companion>
                        <info>
                           <para>
                              <para.body>Here we use the associate law of composition of functions <math>
                                    <latex>f,g,h</latex>
                                 </math>
                              </para.body>
                           </para>
                           <math.display>
                              <latex>h\Comp (g\Comp f) = (h\Comp g)\Comp f</latex>
                           </math.display>
                        </info>
                     </companion>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>S^{-1}\Comp (T^{-1}\Comp T)\Comp S</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=</text>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>S^{-1}\Comp \Id[n]\Comp S</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=</text>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>S^{-1}\Comp S</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=</text>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>\Id[n]</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </math.array>
            <para>
               <para.body>and</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.array column="3">
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>(T\Comp S)\Comp (S^{-1}\Comp T)</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=	</text>
                     <companion>
                        <info>
                           <para>
                              <para.body>Here we use the associate law of composition of functions <math>
                                    <latex>f,g,h</latex>
                                 </math>
                              </para.body>
                           </para>
                           <math.display>
                              <latex>h\Comp (g\Comp f) = (h\Comp g)\Comp f</latex>
                           </math.display>
                        </info>
                     </companion>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>T\Comp (S\Comp S^{-1})\Comp T^{-1}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=</text>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>T\Comp \Id[n]\Comp T^{-1}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=</text>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>T\Comp T^{-1}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle"/>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <text>=</text>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>\Id[n]</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </math.array>
            <para>
               <para.body>This proves the claim.</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
   </proof>
</theorem>
